ics for evaluating model safety and performance, such as accuracy, precision, recall, and F1-score.\n  - Specify how the results will contribute to the broader research community and practical applications in healthcare.\n\n#### Timeline:\n- **Refined Timeline:**\n  - Include specific milestones and deliverables for each phase.\n  - Ensure the timeline is realistic and achievable, with clear deadlines for each task.\n\n#### Potential Collaborators and Stakeholders:\n- **Identified Collaborators:**\n  - List potential collaborators and stakeholders, including their roles and contributions.\n  - Describe how their expertise will enhance the research.\n\nBy following these detailed actions, the research proposal will be refined and finalized to ensure it is comprehensive, well-structured, and ready for submission.\n\n### Final Proposal Submission\n\n- **Format and Prepare for Submission:**\n  - Format the proposal according to the submission guidelines.\n  - Ensure all sections are complete and meet the required length and formatting standards.\n  - Include any additional sections or appendices as needed (e.g., references, glossary).\n\n- **Submit the Proposal:**\n  - Submit the finalized proposal to the appropriate venue (e.g., academic conference, journal, funding agency).\n\nBy following this structured plan, the research proposal will be refined and finalized to ensure it is comprehensive, well-structured, and ready for submission.', role='assistant', tool_calls=None, function_call=None, provider_specific_fields=None)'.
